                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A creature Strides in the engine nacelle</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> The creature's clothing or limbs get caught in the spinning gears and axles of the engine. The creature must attempt a @Check[type:reflex|dc:24] save.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes [[/r {2d8+9}[bludgeoning]]]{2d8+9 bludgeoning damage}.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes [[/r {4d8+18}[bludgeoning]]]{4d8+18 bludgeoning damage}.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature's clothing is pulled into the clockworks. The creature takes [[/r {4d8+18}[bludgeoning]]]{4d8+18 bludgeoning damage} and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Restrained]{Restrained}. Until the creature @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Escape]{Escapes} (DC 24), it takes [[/r {2d8+9}[bludgeoning]]]{2d8+9 bludgeoning damage} each round as it's pulled into the spinning rotors. A creature wearing clothing can automatically Escape by doffing its caught clothing; this destroys the doffed clothing.</p>"
